Doctor of Nurse Anesthesia Practice Program
The application period for summer 2019 start is now open.
Before you start, please have the following items on hand:
The names and email addresses of your references
You will need to complete the entire application at one time to save and submit it. The application will take about 20-30 minutes to complete.
Step 2: Provide Additional Required Admission Materials
After you submit your application, you will receive a confirmation email with a list of additional items to submit.

An official transcript from each college or university where you earned credits must be sent directly to Bryan College of Health Sciences. Many institutions offer a transcript request service on their website. If that is not available, please contact the college(s) or university(
) you attended and have them mail your transcript directly to Bryan College of Health Sciences.
from each of the following people
A person who knows you professionally and personally and is not related to you
to provide accurate information on your clinical skills, experience and ability to pursue graduate study.

Send a personal statement to the Admissions Committee about your interest in this profession, specific reasons you wish to attend Bryan College of Health Sciences School of Nurse Anesthesia and any other relevant information. Please limit to one page

View our campus in-person or from the comfort of your home
Come and learn about the extraordinary opportunities and welcoming community of students, faculty and staff available to you at Bryan College of Health Sciences.

During your campus visit, you will receive a tour of our state-of-the-art learning facility and speak with a member of the admissions team about the application process, transfer/dual enrollment credit, financial aid and any other questions you may have about becoming a Future Healer. You will also have opportunities to get to know our faculty, staff and programs first-hand, including meeting with a faculty member and sitting in on a class when scheduling allows. Call the admissions office at

Visit campus from your computer or mobile device by taking our interactive 360 degree tour. Step inside a classroom, get up-close to our human plastinates in our science lab, or see what current students are up to in our student lounges.
